Key Match Events: England routed Oman for 47 in 80 balls
Adil Rashid took 4 wickets for 11 runs
Jofra Archer and Mark Wood took 2 wickets each
Jos Buttler scored 24 not out from 8 balls
Pre-Game Insights: England needed to win quickly to boost their net run-rate
Buttler decided to bowl first to know how many runs they were chasing
England's quicks flexed in the powerplay to reduce Oman to 25 for 4
Post-Match Reflections: England are back in the game after a ruthless dispatching of Oman
Scotland will face a daunting task to beat Group B leaders Australia
England's quicks and Rashid's four-wicket haul led to a comprehensive win
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's win means they can go past Scotland's NRR if they win their next match in 5.2 overs or less
Phil Salt gave the impression that a 1.2-over finish was realistic before being dismissed
